    <abstract>For Mount Jian, Wu Shifen (1796-1856) listed altogether 17 inscriptions. These include the misplaced inscription from Mount Gang (probably copied from Ruan Yuan’s Shanzuo jinshi zhi), three inscription from Pot Stand Rocks (Zhiguoshi 支鍋石), and 13 from the actual slope at “Great Buddha Ridge”. For some of these entries a location is given, for some not.</abstract>
